      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a vital constitutional safeguard that protects fundamental liberties from government overreach. It ensures that the government cannot infringe upon deeply rooted rights, even if the procedures for taking those rights are technically followed. This doctrine has been crucial in expanding civil rights by striking down laws that infringe upon personal autonomy and basic freedoms. It is a powerful tool for preserving individual liberty against legislative tyranny.",
